'''Derrick Luckassen''' (born 3 July 1995) is a professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[centre-back]] for Cypriot club [[Pafos FC|Pafos]]. Born in the Netherlands, he plays for the [[Ghana national football team|Ghana national team]].

==Club career==
===AZ===
Luckassen is a graduate of the [[AZ Alkmaar|AZ]] youth academy. He captained the youth team during the 2013–14 campaign.<ref>{{cite web|title=Luckassen hoopt op doorbraak bij AZ|url=http://www.voetbal.com/news/_n1199997_/luckassen-hoopt-op-doorbraak-bij-az/|publisher=Voetbal|access-date=10 October 2014}}</ref> On 29 August 2014, he signed a professional contract with the club, keeping him there until 2018.<ref>{{cite web|title=Luckassen contract|url=https://twitter.com/AZAlkmaar/status/505365013184651264/photo/1|publisher=AZ Alkmaar via Twitter|access-date=10 October 2014}}</ref>

Luckassen made his professional debut for the club against [[FC Dordrecht|Dordrecht]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Dordetch vs AZ|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2014/08/30/netherlands/eredivisie/bvo-fc-dordrecht/stichting-az/1690533/|publisher=Soccerway|access-date=10 October 2014}}</ref> He first played a whole match against [[FC Twente|Twente]].<ref>{{cite web|title=AZ vs Twente|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2014/10/05/netherlands/eredivisie/stichting-az/stichting-fc-twente-65/1690613/|publisher=Soccerway|access-date=10 October 2014}}</ref>

===PSV Eindhoven ===
On 10 July 2017, Luckassen moved to league rivals [[PSV Eindhoven|PSV]] on a five-year deal until 2022.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.psv.nl/psv/nieuws/artikel/derrick-luckassen-voor-vijf-jaar-naar-psv.htm|title=Derrick Luckassen voor vijf jaar naar PSV|website=psv.nl|language=nl|access-date=10 July 2017|archive-date=19 November 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171119025723/http://www.psv.nl/psv/nieuws/artikel/derrick-luckassen-voor-vijf-jaar-naar-psv.htm|url-status=dead}}</ref>

He came off the bench on 15 April 2018 as PSV beat rivals Ajax 3–0 to clinch the [[2017–18 Eredivisie]] title.<ref>{{cite news |title=PSV Eindhoven beat Ajax to seal title |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/43776657 |access-date=28 August 2018 |work=BBC Sport |date=15 April 2018}}</ref>

====Loan to Hertha Berlin====
On 28 August 2018, Luckassen moved to [[Bundesliga]] side [[Hertha BSC]] on a season-long loan for the [[2018–19 Bundesliga|season]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Derrick Luckassen arrives on loan |url=https://www.herthabsc.de/en/teams/luckassen-signing/page/822--4-4-.html |website=Hertha BSC |access-date=28 August 2018 |date=28 August 2018 |archive-date=29 August 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180829000319/https://www.herthabsc.de/en/teams/luckassen-signing/page/822--4-4-.html |url-status=dead }}</ref>

==== Loan to Anderlecht ====
On 31 August 19, Luckassen was loaned to Belgium side [[R.S.C. Anderlecht|Anderlecht]] on a season-long loan.<ref>{{Cite web|date=31 August 2019|title=Derrick Luckassen moves to Anderlecht on loan|url=https://www.besoccer.com/new/derrick-luckassen-moves-to-anderlecht-on-loan-699742|access-date=11 January 2021|website=BeSoccer|archive-date=17 November 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191117154548/https://www.besoccer.com/new/derrick-luckassen-moves-to-anderlecht-on-loan-699742|url-status=dead}}</ref> On 6 June 2020, [[PSV Eindhoven]] agreed to loan Luckassen to [[R.S.C. Anderlecht|Anderlecht]] for another season.<ref>{{Cite web|date=6 July 2020|title=PSV agree to loan Ghanaian defender Derrick Luckassen to Anderlecht for another season|url=https://ghanasoccernet.com/psv-agree-to-loan-ghanaian-defender-derrick-luckassen-to-anderlecht-for-another-season|access-date=11 January 2021|website=Ghana SoccerNet}}</ref>

====Loan to Kasımpaşa====
On 11 January 2021, due to a lack of playing time Luckassen ended his loan at [[R.S.C. Anderlecht|Anderlecht]], and moved to Turkish club, [[Kasımpaşa S.K.|Kasımpaşa]], on loan until the end of June.<ref>{{Cite web|date=11 January 2021|title=RSC Anderlecht: Derrick Luckassen quitte le club après un an et demi|trans-title=RSC Anderlecht: Derrick Luckassen leaves the club after a year and a half|url=https://bx1.be/sport/rsc-anderlecht-derrick-luckassen-quitte-le-club-apres-un-an-et-demi/|access-date=11 January 2021|website=bx1 Médias de Bruxelles|language=fr}}</ref>

====Loan to Fatih Karagümrük====
On 9 June 2021, he returned to Turkey on a new loan, joining [[Fatih Karagümrük S.K.|Fatih Karagümrük]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[PSV Eindhoven]]|url=https://www.psv.nl/english-psv/news/article/luckassen-joins-fatih-karagumruk-on-loan.htm|title=LUCKASSEN JOINS FATIH KARAGÜMRÜK ON LOAN|date=9 June 2021|accessdate=30 September 2021}}</ref>

===Pafos===
On 20 July 2024, [[Cypriot First Division|Cypriot]] club [[Pafos FC|Pafos]] announced the signing of Luckassen from [[Maccabi Tel Aviv F.C.|Maccabi Tel Aviv]].<ref name="Derrick Luckassen">{{cite web |title=DERRICK LUCKASSEN JOINS PAFOS FC! |url=https://pafosfc.com.cy/derrick-luckassen-joins-pafos-fc/ |website=pafosfc.com.cy |publisher=Pafos FC |access-date=22 July 2024 |date=20 July 2024}}</ref> He was part of the Pafos side that won the club's first Cypriot league title during the [[2024–25 Cypriot First Division|2024–25 season]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/articles/cj6x7rrxzedo|title=Pafos FC: Who are Champions League debutants|website=BBC|date=17 September 2025|access-date=18 September 2025}}</ref>

On 5 November 2025, Luckassen helped Pafos to their first ever win in the [[UEFA Champions League|Champions League]] proper as they stunned [[La Liga]] side [[Villarreal CF|Villarreal]]. Luckassen scored the historic winner with a header following a corner from winger [[Ken Sema]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/c2kppg4n95wt|title=Pafos 1-0 Villarreal: Hosts claim historic first Champions League win|website=BBC|date=5 November 2025|access-date=12 November 2025}}</ref>

==International career==
Luckassen was born in the Netherlands to parents of [[Ghana]]ian descent, and has represented the Netherlands at youth level.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.football-oranje.com/luckassen-hoping-psv-move/|title=Luckassen hoping for PSV move - Football Oranje|date=1 June 2016}}</ref>
In March 2026, Luckassen was called up by [[Ghana national football team|Ghana]] for their [[Exhibition game|friendly]] matches against [[Austria national football team|Austria]] and [[Germany national football team|Germany]].<ref>{{cite web |title=PHOTOS: Black Stars begin Austria friendly Preparation with 21 players training in Vienna |url=https://www.ghanafa.org/photos-black-stars-begin-austria-friendly-preparation-with-21-players-training-in-vienna |website=ghanafa.org |publisher=Ghana Football Association |access-date=24 March 2026 |date=24 March 2026}}</ref>

Luckassen was named in the Ghana squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]] on 2 June 2026 after being called up as a replacement for the injured [[Alexander Djiku]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.ghanafa.org/carlos-queiroz-names-2026-fifa-world-cup-squad |title=Carlos Queiroz names 2026 FIFA World Cup squad |publisher=[[Ghana Football Association]] |date=June 2, 2026 |access-date=June 2, 2026 |archive-date=June 2, 2026 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20260602044349/https://www.ghanafa.org/carlos-queiroz-names-2026-fifa-world-cup-squad |url-status=live }}</ref>

==Personal life==
Luckassen is the brother of [[Kevin Brobbey]], who like Derrick, started his professional career at AZ Alkmaar, and [[Brian Brobbey]], all footballers.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.az.nl/nieuws/wie-wat-waar-luckassen-hupperts-van-der-velden/1|title=Wie Wat Waar: Luckassen, Hupperts, Van der Velden|publisher=AZ Alkmaar|language=Dutch|date=1 May 2017|accessdate=18 May 2018|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180513201436/https://www.az.nl/nieuws/wie-wat-waar-luckassen-hupperts-van-der-velden/1|archivedate=13 May 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>

